  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Thrombopoietin Receptor Agonists (TPO-ra) are novel treatment modalities for patients with
      refractory Primary Immune Thrombocytopenia (ITP), but only few data are available for
      long-term effects of these drugs. In this observational study, effects and adverse effects
      including evaluation of bone marrow biopsies done at fixed intervals will be recorded from
      ITP patients treated with TPO-ra. For some patients, blood samples will be collected for
      research use.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
