    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adult patients with ITP

          -  platelet counts &lt; 25 x10*9/L or &lt; 50 x10*9/L with bleeding symptoms

          -  meets criteria for treatment with TPO-ra

          -  Females must use contraceptives when applicable for at least three months before
             inclusion

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy or nursing

          -  Former thromboembolic events excluding one incidence of deep venous thrombosis as
             complication to surgery or pregnancy or one incidence of cerebral embolism as
             complication to atrial fibrillation

          -  Liver insufficiency (for eltrombopag only)

          -  TPO-ra contraindications (e.g. allergy)

          -  TPO-ra treatments less than 6 months prior to inclusion
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
